gomodel:SYNGO_2342  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" , "Rationale: Figure 2\na) triple-immunofluorescence staining of cultured Shisa6 KO for Flag-Shisa6, Gria2, Dlg4 shows Shisa6 co-localizes with AMPARs and PSD-95 at postsynaptic sites\nd) biochemical fractionation shows Shisa6 is enriched in PSD\ne,f) IP+WB shows co-immunoprecipitation of AMPAR and Shisa6\n\nFigure 3 further supportes postsynaptic localization by demonstrating Shisa6-Dlg4 interaction.\n\n\"integral component\" based on the protein's transmembrane domain. Experimental description: IPs from Figure 2 were performed on mice; \"Precipitation of protein complexes from mouse hippocampus\"\n\nimmunofluorescence imaging in Figure 2 and FRET assay of Figure 3 was performed on rat cultures; \"Hippocampal neurons derived from 18-day-old rat embryos of either sex were cultured following the Banker protocol\"\n\n24/01/2018 Pim\n- The neurons in Fig.2 are mouse neurons expressing a mouse protein: \"Triple-immunofluorescence staining of a cultured Shisa6 KO neuron (DIV16), expressing inducible Flag-tagged Shisa6 for 18 h, ...\"\n- Tissue prep in Fig.2 is mouse species: \"... insoluble fraction) of mature mouse hippocampus reveals an enrichment of Shisa6 in the PSD t...\"\n- Over-expressed Shisa6 is of mouse species: \"The full-length coding DNA for exon3-containing mouse Shisa6 was obtained from Genscript as a pENTR4 construct (\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2342" ;
